-- Canadian Stocks Decline, Erasing Earlier Gain, as RIM Retreats
-- B y   S t e p h e n   K l e e g e
-- 2010-11-01T19:16:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/canadian-stocks-decline-erasing-earlier-gain-as-research-in-motion-falls.html
Canadian stocks fell, erasing an
earlier gain, as Research In Motion Ltd. and Barrick Gold Corp.
declined.  The Standard & Poor’s/TSX Composite Index fell 16.01 point,
or 0.1 percent, to 12,660.23 at 3:11 p.m. in Toronto. The
benchmark gained as much as 0.7 percent earlier.  Research In Motion, maker of the BlackBerry smart phone,
fell 1.8 percent to C$56.95. Barrick, the world’s biggest gold
producer, slipped 0.6 percent to C$48.82.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Kleege at 
 skleege@bloomberg.net  